Here are both approaches:

## 1. Route Registration (AppShell.xaml.cs)

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

## 2. Navigate from ProductListPage

```csharp
// APPROACH A â€” string query parameter
async void OnProductSelected(object sender, SelectionChangedEventArgs e)
{
    if (e.CurrentSelection.FirstOrDefault() is Product product)
    {
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");
    }
}

// APPROACH B â€” pass the full object
async void OnProductSelected(object sender, SelectionChangedEventArgs e)
{
    if (e.CurrentSelection.FirstOrDefault() is Product product)
    {
        var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        {
            { "product", product }
        };
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
    }
}
```

## 3. Receive on the ViewModel with IQueryAttributable

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // APPROACH A â€” string parameter arrives as a string value
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID
        }

        // APPROACH B â€” full object arrives as-is (no serialization)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
        }
    }
}
```

## 4. Wire BindingContext on the Page

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?productId=42`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| Data type | String only | Any object |
| Serialization | URI-encoded | None (passed by reference) |
| Use when | Simple IDs/flags | Complex or large objects |

Both approaches deliver data to the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` method â€” you can even combine them in one navigation call. Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
